description:
&lt;h1&gt;Targeted Mental Health Outreach Workers                                                 &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: £23,647 p.a. pro rata&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time permanent contracts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TaMHS are Swindon’s Tier 2 CAMHS service, we work with Children and Young People from 0-18 to deliver short term evidenced based interventions to improve their mental health and emotional well-being.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of this innovative team you will currently be based remotely and work under the supervision of the Senior Clinical Practitioners to deliver a range of individual interventions in school settings. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an opportunity for two Outreach Worker positions. With a certificate or diploma in childcare or education, or equivalent, and relevant experience of working with children, young people and families in a multi-agency setting, you will also have a good understanding of how mental health issues can impact emotional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for a managing your own caseload of children and young people between the ages of 5- 18 for which you will co-ordinate care in conjunction with other professionals in the Early Help teams, schools, voluntary sector and CAMHS.  You will also undertake assessments and short term therapeutic intervention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should also possess excellent communication skills and the ability to develop relationships with professionals, young people and their families. IT proficiency is important as is your ability to work creatively and on your own initiative. In return you can expect our commitment to your continuing professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; An enhanced DBS disclosure will be requested for the successful applicants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be fluent in the English language (as a requirement of Part 7 of the Immigration Act – for the effective performance of a customer-facing role).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion about the role, please contact Danielle Kemp, Professional Lead dkemp@swindon.gov.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 16 November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview: 20 November 2020 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
